        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 3:44PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lima, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lima, Monida, and Snowline. This includes Interstate 15 from Lima to
Monida Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
